# BigBit bridge allow-list (KEEP-SYNC). One line per table:
#   AccessTable | pg_target | sql_file (in sql/)
# The deny-list (EXCLUDE-TVRDO in F3) is enforced by simply NOT listing tables
# here - the script never mdb-export-s anything outside this manifest.
#
# Column order in each sql/*.sql staging table MUST match the Access table's
# storage order (mdb-export emits all columns in that order; \copy loads
# positionally after skipping the header).
#
# --- v0 pilot: 3 item classifier tables (models existed in 2.0 but were never
#     synced - items had group/subgroup/origin CODES without NAMES, F1 gap) ---
R_Grupa    | item_groups    | item_groups.sql
R_Podgrupa | item_subgroups | item_subgroups.sql
R_Poreklo  | item_origins   | item_origins.sql
#
# --- phase 2 (ID-space RESOLVED, plan 7.6 = option A). Order matters: masters
#     before Cenovnik (Cenovnik remaps item via items.external_item_id).
Magacini   | warehouses     | warehouses.sql
# Komitenti  | customers          | customers.sql          (dual-writer: MSSQL sync owns customers; dry-run first)
# Predmeti   | projects           | projects.sql           (dual-writer; dry-run first)
# R_Artikli  | items              | items.sql              (UPDATE-only via external_item_id while MSSQL sync runs)
# Cenovnik   | price_list_entries | price_list_entries.sql (two-step remap; after items)
#     (Prodavci: NEVER expose [Password] - plain-text; needs a projection since
#      mdb-export dumps the whole table).
# --- phase 3: the rest of KEEP-SYNC from BB_T_26-analiza-F3-inventar-207-tabela.md
